But as soon as <COREF ID="23" TYPE="IDENT">the accords</COREF> were signed , American officials sharply reduced <COREF ID="15" TYPE="IDENT">aid</COREF> .
In February 1989 , when <COREF ID="27" TYPE="IDENT">the Soviets</COREF> said <COREF ID="27" TYPE="IDENT">they</COREF> had completed <COREF ID="13" TYPE="IDENT"><COREF ID="27" TYPE="IDENT">their</COREF> pullout</COREF> , <COREF ID="32" TYPE="IDENT">the U.S.</COREF> cut <COREF ID="15" TYPE="IDENT">it</COREF> further .
